						               													<description>&amp;quot;If you start with a box of spiders, pretty soon you're left with one mean looking spider.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;BoS is played with a standard deck of playing cards, including two jokers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deal the cards into  6x9 grid; this forms the playing area.  Number cards should be dealt face-up.  Picture cards and jokers should be dealt face down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Standard 2 player game:&amp;#10;- Player 1 has the red number cards (red spiders)&amp;#10;- Player 2 has the black number cards (black spiders)&amp;#10;- Court cards and jokers are flies&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn consists of a player making a capture:&amp;#10;- The player moves a spider of their colour over any number of friendly pieces and empty spaces onto any fly or an enemy spider of equal or lower value.&amp;#10;- Movement is orthogonal only &amp;#10;- If no capture is posible, the player must pass&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When both players pass, the game ends.  Players score 1 point for each remaining spider of their colour, and 1 point for each captured card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3-4 player rules:&amp;#10;Each player gets the number cards in 1 suit.  In a 3 player game, there will be a neutral colour of spider.  These do not move, but can be captured according to the normal rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
